Morphology. General features —Idiosoma roundish; shoulder platelet elongated (shoulder/frontal platelets L ratio 1.7–1.9 ); frontal margin medially with large anterolaterally pointed apodemes (
Figs. 18 D–E
); Cxgl- 4 located far anteriorly, near tips of Cx-I; gnathosomal bay V-shaped; suture line of Cx-IV distinct, originating from lateral edge of genital field; line of primary sclerotization close to posterior margin of genital field; excretory pore and Vgl- 2 well separated from the line of primary sclerotization, Vgl- 2 posterior to excretory pore; gnathosoma elongated in lateral view, rostrum truncated (
Fig. 19 E
); P- 2 shorter than P- 4 , ventral and dorsal setae of P- 2 and P- 3 relatively strong and long, P- 2 and P- 3 distal margins without pointed tips; P- 4 swollen in distal half, with two ventral setae, one of which is very long and away from distal edge (
Figs. 19 A–B
). Male: medial margin of Cx-II/III relatively short; genital field small and rounded, ejaculatory complex with small proximal chamber, carina anterior long (
Figs. 19 D
,
44 A
). Female: genital field large and rounded.

Distribution. West Africa: Cameroon (
K. Viets 1958
), Liberia (
Cook 1966
), Ghana (new record).
